<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">407. Lightolier Inc. Lessons in Lighting: A Basic Course. Jersey City, NY, 1982. Variously paginated. Index, bibl., glossary, B/W illus. </p><p class="annot">This loose-leaf notebook produced by a manufacturer of lightingproducts consists of 24 three-page lessons that briefly summarize lighting concepts and conclude with references and study questions. Lessons cover vision, color and light sources, use of lighting, and technical information about electricity and maintenance of lighting systems. The format of this instructive overview breaks complex information into manageable segments.</p></div>
